The vast majority of positions at the IRS are considered career roles, with only the commissioner and chief counsel being politically appointed. Sacco holds a key role at the IRS, where he interprets how convoluted federal tax law is applied in specific situations. Sacco was brought on by the Biden administration as a career employee in September 2022. The vast majority of positions at the IRS are considered career roles, with only the commissioner and chief counsel being politically appointed. Before joining the IRS, Sacco worked under Oregon Democratic Senator Ron Wyden for the Senate Finance Committee, according to his LinkedIn. READ MORE: Top IRS Lawyer Unde
